Unique elements will have only one count in the map.
Thus, to find the maximum number of elements in the map, you can iterate through the map and find the maximum value.
class Solution {
    public int maxFrequencyElements(int[] nums) {
        int maxFreq = 0;
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            map.put(nums[i], map.getOrDefault(nums[i], 0) + 1);
        }
        for (int count : map.values()) {
            maxFreq = Math.max(maxFreq, count);
        }
        int res = 0;
        for (int count : map.values()) {
            if (count == maxFreq) {
                res += count;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}

